        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-15 10:39:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooks to be a defect in how cpumask_of_node() is detected. I will update the patch to fix it.\n\nchecking whether have cpumask_of_node... no\n\n/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/i686/build_type/client/distro/el5/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/BUILD/lustre-2.3.54/lustre/include/linux/lustre_compat25.h:658:1: error: \"cpumask_of_node\" redefined\n\n/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/i686/build_type/client/distro/el5/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/kernel-ib-devel/usr/src/ofa_kernel/kernel_addons/backport/2.6.18-EL5.6/include//linux/cpumask.h:7:1: error: this is the location of the previous definition",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "55e1817d194ab19bc9a9a21fb68fd2d35a81b026",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-15 11:52:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI downloaded 2.6.18-308.20.1.el5.i686 kernel source, but found that it doesn't have cpumask_of_node(). I'll send an updated version of patch. It should address the build error but I can't verify it myself...\n\nBTW, is Jenkins using a self-patched kernel? If so, can I download it somewhere?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "65a54fb5572ca4393c69fc9b618e77f1660e3a6b",
      "author": {
