    {
      "id": "219808953f2adf6f2488f216e2d219c7309df590",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-16 02:03:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI didn't check out the build failure, but the patch looks reasonable. \n\nThere is one place where there could be tabs for indentation between two modified lines, but I can't point it out directly via my phone.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "21d70a23bc66db2ae7a6e94505a15894fde2465b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-16 04:05:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe second patch got the same build error, failing to detect cpumask_of_node().\n\nNow I understand the build error. It is because OFED backports cpumask_of_node() in its own linux/cpumask.h, whereas <linux/cpumask.h> only includes the in-kernel one.\n\nI'll update the patch to fix it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
