        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-16 18:06:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIt seems in the RHEL5 ofa build it seems there was some trouble with cfs_node_to_cpumask and friends. \n\n/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el5/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/BUILD/lustre-2.3.54/libcfs/libcfs/linux/linux-cpu.c: In function 'cfs_node_to_cpumask':\n/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el5/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/BUILD/lustre-2.3.54/libcfs/libcfs/linux/linux-cpu.c:147: error: implicit declaration of function 'cpumask_copy'",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e755ce4dc60971832f4788f0bb10af49772e089d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-19 04:44:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nYeah, ./configure checks cpumask_of_node() and assumes that cpumask_copy() is always alone with cpumask_of_node(). However, ofa kernel backports only cpumask_of_node but leaves cpumask_copy out.\n\nI'll update and fix it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
